<typeStatus box="[196,256,1181,1207]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In Schoenherr’s collection at 
<collectionCode box="[631,720,1181,1207]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8z6v-f8is" name="Saskatchewan Museum of Natural History" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">SMNH</collectionCode>
, under the name “ 
<emphasis box="[941,1066,1181,1206]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName box="[941,1061,1181,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="motacilla">Motacilla</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
Schh., 
<number box="[1158,1235,1181,1207]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="20.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="16.0">16–25</number>
, Bhn.” is a male (pinned through the right elytron, left middle and right fore tarsi beyond segment 
<number box="[1133,1148,1218,1244]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
, right hind leg missing) bearing the handwritten label: “Caucasus, Ménétries”, and fitting description with 
<typeStatus box="[1111,1161,1256,1282]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
locality as Caucasus. It is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[400,507,1293,1319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">lectotype</typeStatus>
with“ 
<typeStatus box="[578,713,1293,1319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
, 
<number box="[724,746,1292,1318]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schh., Gultekin" authorityName="Schh., Gultekin" box="[761,1133,1293,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="motacilla">
<emphasis box="[761,942,1293,1318]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Lixus motacilla</emphasis>
Schh., Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number box="[1193,1258,1293,1319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2006.0">2006</number>
”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1143,1431]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,318,1330,1356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
The authorship of this species is 
<bibRefCitation author="Schoenherr" box="[718,1000,1330,1356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="21" refString="Schoenherr, C. J. (1832) In: Menetries, E. (1832). Catalogue raisonne des objects de zoologie recuillis dans un voyage au Caucase et jusqu'aux frontieres actuelles de la Perse entrepris par ordre de S. M. l'Empereur. St. Petersbourg, [4] + 271 + XII + IV + [1] pp." type="journal article" year="1832">
Schoenherr (
<number box="[870,934,1330,1356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1832.0">1832</number>
: 
<number box="[946,992,1330,1356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="222.0">222</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
not Boheman. In Schoenherr (
<number box="[1368,1432,1330,1356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1835.0">1835</number>
: 
<number box="[151,183,1368,1394]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="14.0">14</number>
), Boheman gave a more detailed redescription. This species is related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1060,1243,1368,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindrus">
<emphasis box="[1060,1243,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Lixus cylindrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(F.), but clearly differs by the shape of rostrum, elytral pattern, sulciform striae and aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
